      },
      {
        "id": "row-tip1",
        "cells": [
          1
        ],
        "columns": [
          {
            "id": "col-tip1",
            "contents": [
              {
                "id": "heading-tip1",
                "type": "heading",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 16px",
                  "headingType": "h2",
                  "fontWeight": 500,
                  "fontSize": "24px",
                  "color": "#D4AF37",
                  "fontFamily": {
                    "label": "Cormorant Garamond",
                    "value": "'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif",
                    "url": "https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant Garamond:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
                  },
                  "textAlign": "left",
                  "lineHeight": "130%",
                  "text": "#1: Trust Your Gut When You Walk In",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip1-1",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 12px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\">Photos only tell you so much. When you visit a venue in person, pay attention to:</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip1-2",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 8px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\"><strong>Can you actually see YOUR wedding happening here?</strong><br/>Not someone else's Pinterest-perfect wedding — <em>yours</em>. The flowers you choose, the people you love gathered around you, your dad giving his toast, your first dance.</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip1-3",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 8px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\"><strong>Does the space feel right for your guest count?</strong><br/>A venue that feels perfect for 100 guests might feel empty for 200, or cramped for 250.</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip1-4",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 8px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\"><strong>Do you feel welcomed, or like you're being sold to?</strong><br/>You'll be working with this team for a year or more. Do they seem genuinely excited about your vision, or just going through the motions?</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip1-5",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 30px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;color:#666666;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;font-style:italic;\">That last one matters more than you'd think. Your venue coordinator becomes part of your wedding planning team — you want someone you're excited to work with.</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              }
            ],
            "values": {}
          }
        ],
        "values": {
          "backgroundColor": "#FFFFFF",
          "columnsBackgroundColor": "",
          "padding": "0px"
        }
