      {
        "id": "row-tip3",
        "cells": [
          1
        ],
        "columns": [
          {
            "id": "col-tip3",
            "contents": [
              {
                "id": "heading-tip3",
                "type": "heading",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 16px",
                  "headingType": "h2",
                  "fontWeight": 500,
                  "fontSize": "24px",
                  "color": "#D4AF37",
                  "fontFamily": {
                    "label": "Cormorant Garamond",
                    "value": "'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif",
                    "url": "https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant Garamond:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
                  },
                  "textAlign": "left",
                  "lineHeight": "130%",
                  "text": "#3: Think About the Planning Process",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip3-1",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 12px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\">Your venue choice determines how you'll spend the next year of your life:</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip3-2",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 8px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\"><strong>Will you be coordinating with five different vendors?</strong><br/>When you book separate venues, caterers, rental companies, bar services, and coordinators, you become the project manager of your own wedding.</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip3-3",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 8px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\"><strong>Who's managing your timeline and setup?</strong><br/>Things go wrong at every wedding — it's how they're handled that matters.</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip3-4",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "0px 40px 8px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\"><strong>If something goes sideways, who fixes it?</strong><br/>The answer should be \"we do\" — not \"that's between you and your vendors.\"</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "text-tip3-5",
                "type": "text",
                "values": {
                  "containerPadding": "16px 40px 30px",
                  "text": "<p style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#4A4A4A;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;margin:0;\">When one experienced team manages everything in one location — as we do at Cameron Estate — planning gets significantly easier. Enjoy the fun and magic of this special season in your life - we will handle behind the scenes to make it all happen.</p>",
                  "hideDesktop": false
                }
              }
            ],
            "values": {}
          }
